    "shortDescription": "Praying mantises are the only insects that can turn their heads all the way around to look behind themselves — handy when you hunt by ambush and need to track fast-moving prey. They sit perfectly still for ages, then strike with their spiked front legs faster than you can blink. Fun fact: A mantis can strike and grab prey in under a hundredth of a second — too fast for the human eye to follow."
